<subSubSection id="7EFD0782FF81014889CF73E6FADA17F5" pageId="19" pageNumber="516" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="36585409FF81014889CF73E6FADA17F5" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis id="0493881BFF81014889CF73E6FE9A1789" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honor of Professor Gangrou Xiao (Forest Research Institute, Chinese Academy of Forestry, 
<collectingRegion id="F4239AEBFF810148889973C2FE3117F6" box="[401,485,439,466]" country="China" name="Beijing" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">Beijing</collectingRegion>
) who is the first Chinese entomologist to study the 
<taxonomicName id="F1E72F8AFF8101488D2E73C2FB4B17F5" box="[1062,1183,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bethylidae</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="4EF01499FF8101488DCC73C2FADF17F5" box="[1220,1291,439,465]" name="China" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7EFD0782FF81014889CF73AFFC4A1419" pageId="19" pageNumber="516" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="36585409FF81014889CF73AFFC4A1419" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis id="0493881BFF81014889CF73AFFE9B17D0" bold="true" box="[199,335,474,500]" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">Comments.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other species of this genus by having median clypeal lobe distinctly protuberant and narrow (
<figureCitation id="AEDC488CFF8101488B2E738AFDAC143D" box="[550,632,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,181,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[162,1425,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 8. Odontepyris xiaoi sp. nov. holotype, ♂. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Median clypeal carina; d. Mandible; e. Antenna; f. Pronotum, dorsal view; g. Mesosoma, lateral view; h. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; i. Forewing; j. Hypopygium; k. Genitalia, dorsal view; l. Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.15 mm for a–l." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4715419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4715419/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
), median clypeal carina not exceeding anterior imaginary line of eyes (
<figureCitation id="AEDC488CFF81014889A87056FF3A1419" box="[160,238,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,181,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[162,1425,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 8. Odontepyris xiaoi sp. nov. holotype, ♂. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Median clypeal carina; d. Mandible; e. Antenna; f. Pronotum, dorsal view; g. Mesosoma, lateral view; h. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; i. Forewing; j. Hypopygium; k. Genitalia, dorsal view; l. Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.15 mm for a–l." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4715419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4715419/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
) and mesopleural dentate process present but weak (
<figureCitation id="AEDC488CFF8101488A367056FC451419" box="[830,913,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,181,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-29@18.[162,1425,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 8. Odontepyris xiaoi sp. nov. holotype, ♂. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Median clypeal carina; d. Mandible; e. Antenna; f. Pronotum, dorsal view; g. Mesosoma, lateral view; h. Metapectal-propodeal complex, dorsal view; i. Forewing; j. Hypopygium; k. Genitalia, dorsal view; l. Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.15 mm for a–l." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4715419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4715419/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="516">
Fig. 
<quantity id="F11FF9ECFF8101488A7A7056FC451419" box="[882,913,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="8.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="516" unit="g" value="8.0">8g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
